              "latency_ms": 2220.9936670260504,
              "response": "The layered architecture pattern used in Snipara consists of the following hierarchy:\n\n1. **Routes (app/api/)** - The top layer that handles API routes.\n2. **Services (lib/services/)** - This layer contains external API adapters.\n3. **Repositories (lib/db/queries/)** - This layer is responsible for centralized CRUD operations.\n4. **Utils & Types** - The bottom layer that has no dependencies.\n\nThis hierarchy ensures that lower layers cannot import from higher layers, maintaining a clear separation of concerns (as stated in the \"Import hierarchy\" section).",
